<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 21 at 4:56AM CDT until July 21 at 5:15AM CDT by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 515 AM CDT
FOR SOUTH CENTRAL KAY AND EASTERN NOBLE COUNTIES...
At 455 AM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 5 miles northeast of Marland to 3 miles northeast of
Sooner Lake to 3 miles north of Glencoe, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Ponca City, Morrison, Red Rock, Marland, Sooner Lake, and Ceres.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
